I love you all so much, and again thank you.

As I watch my Dad lay my brothers ashes in his final resting place today it put so many things into perspective for me. It has been almost 6 years without him, but it almost feels like no time has passed at all. Grief is strange, but life is beautiful, and I know he knows how much we celebrate who he was. While we were on the side of this cliff a crow flew overhead and I think that was his way of letting us know. He’s always with us in someway. I share these experiences in hopes it helps all of you. I love you all.
